The article is a report from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Speaker of the House and potentially the President (Dear Mr. Speaker, Dear Madam President). The report discusses recent attacks by militia groups affiliated with Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps (IRGC) against US personnel and facilities in Iraq and Syria. The President authorized targeted strikes against IRGC facilities in Syria and Iraq to deter future attacks and protect US personnel. The strikes were conducted in a manner to limit the risk of escalation and civilian casualties. The President directed these actions to defend US personnel, degrade and disrupt attacks, and deter Iran and its militia groups from further supporting attacks. The report emphasizes that the military action was consistent with international law and the US's right of self-defense. The President states that the US is prepared to take further action as necessary and appreciates the support of Congress.